1 c. Shall develop a pilot program to support a business operating or seeking to
2 create an apprenticeship program under the federal apprenticeship system.
3 d. May contract with other state agencies to develop and administer programs to
4 assist the state director from the office of apprenticeship of the United States
5 department of labor in promoting entrance in the federal apprenticeship system.
6 5. This section does not apply to an apprenticeship program maintained, managed, or
7 overseen by any state board or commission in this state.
8 SECTION 2. APPROPRIATION - DEPARTMENT OF LABOR AND HUMAN RIGHTS -
9 DIVISION OF APPRENTICESHIP - FULL-TIME EQUIVALENT POSITIONS - REPORT TO
10 THE SEVENTIETH LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY. There is appropriated out of any moneys in the
11 general fund in the state treasury, not otherwise appropriated, the sum of $650,000, or so much
12 of the sum as may be necessary, to the department of labor and human rights for the purpose
13 of providing salaries and benefits for the division of apprenticeship staff, for the biennium
14 beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. The department of labor and human rights is
15 authorized three full-time equivalent positions to administer the division of apprenticeship. The
16 department of labor and human rights shall report to the seventieth legislative assembly
17 regarding the number of apprentices and employers assisted through the division of
18 apprenticeship and the number of new apprenticeship programs created during the 2025-27
19 biennium.
